    <title>Fixed rings of generalized Weyl algebras</title>
    <summary>  We study actions by filtered automorphisms on classical generalized Weyl
algebras (GWAs). In the case of a defining polynomial of degree two, we prove
that the fixed ring under the action of a finite cyclic group of filtered
automorphisms is again a classical GWA, extending a result of Jordan and Wells.
Partial results are provided for the case of higher degree polynomials. In
addition, we establish a version of Auslander's theorem for finite cyclic
groups of filtered automorphisms acting on classical GWAs.
</summary>
